[normal]Evidence  [bold]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]58% of FOD population reside in small rurally isolated settlements with little or no public transport provision. 20% of residents in over half of the districts wards are over the age of 65 (Glos multi-agency MAiDEN data). 
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Accessibility data measuring travel time to 16 service destinations by driving, walking and public transport shows:
[normal]- 70% of the district ranks in the 10% poorest access in the county
[normal]- a quarter in the next 25% poorest access. 
[normal]- 80% of the Forest of Dean
[normal] (FOD)
[normal] is in the worst access quartile for public transport. (MAiDEN).
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]64% of respondents didn’t understand the Community Transport offer, coverage or how to use it.  (Bus Services Review December 2010)
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Out of 41 parishes: five have 50% of the population over 50 years; fifteen parishes have 45% over 50 ( MAiDEN).
[normal]Consultation[bold]-lack of Public/ community transport leading to loneliness, isolation and depression. -older people become housebound/isolated when they physically/ financially cannot run a car
[normal]-better information/alternative options would help people plan for the future. 
[normal]Forest Showcase Event attended by 3,500 people. Consulted 200 people. Detailed feedback from 66 people highlighting:  
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]access issues for young people outside school/training times(12); 
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]transport in their village had been cut or was non-existent (16); 
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]suggestions for enabling marginalised people – ie Dementia (2).  
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]don’t understand Community Transport, how it works, the cost, 
[normal]routes
[normal] (36)
